direction: down

user: User {
  shape: person
  style.fill: "#fdf1d7"
  style.stroke: "#a37a1f"
}

author: Agent writes .d2 text\n(this very diagram) {
  shape: document
}

render: render.sh\nd2 --sketch, font swap,\nresvg to PNG {
  shape: step
  style.fill: "#e3e9fd"
  style.stroke: "#0d32b2"
}

look: Agent reads the PNG\nchecks overlap, clipping,\ntopology

deliver: Deliver .png, .svg, .d2\n(the image you are\nlooking at right now) {
  shape: parallelogram
  style.fill: "#e2f4e2"
  style.stroke: "#1f7a1f"
}

user -> author: types /sketchloop\nhow does sketchloop work?
author -> render
render -> look
look -> author: defects found,\nfix the .d2 {
  style.stroke-dash: 4
}
look -> deliver: clean (2-3 passes max)
